        <tr valign="top">
          <td valign="top"><table width="98%"  border="1" cellpadding="5" cellspacing="5" bordercolor="#AABCCA">
            <tr>
              <td valign="top"><span class="Content_heading">Join Us</span>
                <P align=justify class="careertext">Imagine you are the first to respond to situations such as a gruesome car accident with seriously injured casualties, an armed robbery or a fighting case. Can you remain calm and cool, knowing that innocent lives may be at stake?</P>
                <P align=justify class="careertext">In policing, commitment is important but so is having a cool and sharp mind. If you possess these qualities, we encourage you to join us. You will acquire skills that will turn you into a professional, vested with authority to protect the citizens of Singapore.</P>
                <P align=justify class="career_subheading">Home Team Employee Value Proposition (EVP)</P>
                <P align=justify class="careertext">We offer a rewarding and challenging career to talented men and women who share the Home Team’s mission and want to play an active role in keeping Singapore safe and secure. As a member of the Home Team, you will have the unique opportunity to be involved in real-life safety, law and order and security challenges that confront our society and play an integral role in protecting our country, our community and our loved ones. </P>
                <P align=justify class="careertext">The strength of the Home Team lies in its people. The Home Team is committed to develop every member’s leadership potential and provide an environment where our officers can grow both personally and professionally.</P>
                <P align=justify class="careertext">The Home Team offers a fulfilling and diverse range of career opportunities and experiences. In each of these career paths, our officers will have the opportunity to grow and maximize their potential. It is our belief that every officer will come out richer, more mature and developed individual than when he/she first joined the Home Team.</P></td>
            </tr>
          </table></td>
        </tr>
